## Implementation detail: flag/alias merging

```typescript
// Inside buildListCommand:
const params = builderArgs.parameters ?? {};
const flags = { ...(params.flags ?? {}) };
const aliases = { ...(params.aliases ?? {}) };

// Auto-inject fresh flag (always)
if (!('fresh' in flags)) {
  flags.fresh = FRESH_FLAG;
}

// Auto-inject cursor flag (unless opted out)
if (!options?.noCursorFlag && !('cursor' in flags)) {
  flags.cursor = LIST_CURSOR_FLAG;
}

// Auto-inject aliases
if (!options?.noFreshAlias && !('f' in aliases)) {
  aliases.f = 'fresh';
}
if (!options?.noCursorFlag && !('c' in aliases)) {
  aliases.c = 'cursor';
}

// Wrap func to auto-apply fresh flag
const wrappedFunc = function(this, flags, ...args) {
  applyFreshFlag(flags);
  // ... existing subcommand interception ...
  return originalFunc.call(this, flags, ...args);
};
```

The "if not already present" check means commands that define their own `cursor` flag (like issue list with custom brief) keep theirs — no conflict.

